<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.45.10-12_0001" />

<fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
<note type="authorial">My <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> stuff has recently been shown in New Brunswick! It gets around!</note>

<note type="curatorial">Aly Collection
224-2</note>
<fw type="letterhead">
<hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>
<lb/>
<hi rend="caps">ROUTE 7 SKYRIM FARM</hi>
<lb/>
<hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</hi>  
</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>Feb. 19, 65</dateline>

<salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I'm just back from the University of South Dakota where I made seven more videotapes of my stuff. They now have fifteen half-hour tapes. I was gone a week &#8212; left just as <hi rend="underline">your</hi> letter arrived. I was certainly happy to hear from you again after what seemed a long silence. The Aly family seems to be in a liquid state &#8212; Cornell, Eugene, Hawaii and then? You invited me to make the Hawaii trip with you'ns on March 5th! How I wish I could! &#8212; and I 
<hi rend="double underline">would</hi> if I were not tied here. &#8212; If it were <hi rend="underline">June</hi>! I'm wondering if Bower will be called away from Oregon &#8212;?</p> <note type="authorial">(over)</note>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.45.10-12_0002"/>
<fw type="curatorial">11</fw>

<p>I had a corking time in South Dakota. Lectured four times in addition to the recordings. Read poetry at the men's college in Yankton &#8212; Mount Marty. It was a fine <hi rend="underline">experience</hi>. The nuns were greatly moved by April Theology and Easter. The <del>head</del> head of the College, Sister Teresa, is an enthusiastic fan for The Song of the Messiah &#8212; <hi rend="underline">and</hi> she understands it.</p>

<p>Big preparations are being made for the Neihardt dinner in Bancroft on March 25. I wish <hi rend="underline">you</hi> were going to be there. Also big preparations are being made for the Laureate Tour &#8212; 40 years after!! It has backing from the <del><unclear>Governor</unclear></del>Governor down.</p>
<closer>
<salute><hi rend="underline">Love as always</hi></salute> &#8212; <signed>John N.</signed>
</closer>

</div1>


